'''Staff Corporal''' was a military rank used by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]].

==Behind the scenes==
The rank of Staff Corporal appears only in ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]''.
In the real world, [[Wikipedia:Staff Corporal|Staff Corporal]] is an NCO rank in the [[Wikipedia:Household Division|Household Division]] of the [[Wikipedia:British Army|British Army]], which uses variations on the rank of [[Corporal/Legends|corporal]] for all NCO and Warrant Officer ranks. It is equivalent to an infantry [[Wikipedia:Staff Sergeant|Staff Sergeant]], or in American usage, a [[Wikipedia:United States Army|US Army]] [[Wikipedia:Sergeant First Class|Sergeant First Class]] or a [[Wikipedia:United States Marine Corps|USMC]] [[Wikipedia:|Gunnery Sergeant]].

Where these corporal grades are used for NCOs, the rank for an ordinary soldier is [[Wikipedia:Trooper_(rank)|trooper]]. As "trooper" is widely found in Star Wars, it may have inspired the reference to "Staff Corporal" in ''Galaxies''. However, in [[Star Wars]], it is the rank title alone that is strictly [[canon]]. Where it fits in the rank hierarchy appears not to have been defined.

